Package: poweRcpp
Type: Package
Title: High-Performance Power-Law Distribution Fitting via Rcpp and RcppParallel
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-03-17
Authors@R: person("Angel Luis", "Robles Fernandez",
    email = "a.l.robles.fernandez@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides high-performance fitting of the discrete power-law
    distribution using maximum likelihood estimation and Kolmogorov-Smirnov
    goodness-of-fit testing. The core algorithms are implemented in C++,
    adapted from the 'powerlaw' library, and parallelized with 'RcppParallel'
    for efficient bootstrap goodness-of-fit computation. Supports left-bounded
    (Type I) and right-bounded (Type II) discrete power-law distributions.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Imports:
    Rcpp,
    RcppParallel
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp,
    RcppParallel
SystemRequirements: GNU make
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Encoding: UTF-8
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
